601 UTC ## &#39;2022-12-26T11:03:52.605725Z&#39; Use isoformat() dt.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() ## &#39;2022-12-26T11:03:55.494538&#39; 9.5.4 Attributes print( datetime.now().year ) ## 2022 print( datetime.now().month ) ## 12 print( datetime.now().day ) ## 26 print( datetime.now().hour ) ## 19 print( datetime.now().minute ) ## 3 9.6 time 9.6.1 Constructor print( time(2) ) #default single arugement, hour ## 02:00:00 print( time(2,15) ) #default two arguments, hour, minute ## 02:15:00 print( time(hour=2,minute=15,second=30) ) ## 02:15:30 9.6.2 Class Method 9.6.2.1 now() There is unfortunately no single function to extract the current time. Use time() function of an datetime object datetime.now().time() ## datetime.time(19, 4, 4, 803191) 9.6.3 Attributes print( datetime.now().time().hour ) ## 19 print( datetime.now().time().minute ) ## 4 print( datetime.now().time().second ) ## 8 9.7 timedelta years argument is not supported Apply timedelta on datetime object timedelta cannot be applied on time object , because timedelta potentially go beyond single day (24H) delt = timedelta(days=365,minutes=33,seconds=15) now = datetime.now() print (&#39;delt+now : &#39;, now+delt) ## delt+now : 2023-12-26 19:37:28.367386

